      <br />
      <img class="accommodation-cabin-photos" src="https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/14/79/a8/9c/bus-stop-lounge.jpg" width="60%" alt="accommodation-bus-stop-lounge" /><br /><br /><br />
      <p class="lead mb-4">Bus Stop Lounge</p>
      <p class="lead mb-4 text-justify">
        There are a lot of restaurants close to the marina. One of which we go
        to a lot is the Bus Stop Lounge, where you can enjoy a beautiful view of
        Gzira bay and delicious food with your crew members and trainer. Having
        a local beer Cisk with some snacks is really a pleasure after a day of
        heavy training. Highly recommended!
      </p>
      <img class="accommodation-cabin-photos" src="https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/1b/8c/53/6b/photo0jpg.jpg" width="60%" alt="accommodation-bus-stop-lounge" /><br /><br /><br />
      <br />
      <h4>Recommended to bring</h4>
      <br />
      <p class="lead mb-4 text-justify">
        If you decide to sleep on the boat, please book the cleaning service
        which will include all the bedding and towels for your stay. So
        theortically you don't have to bring anything except your personal wash
        kits and clothes (T-shirts, shorts, swimming suits, fleece or jumper for
        the evenings and windy days at sea).
      </p>
      <p class="lead mb-4 text-justify">
        There are dedicated bathrooms for marina users at the entrance to the
        marina.
      </p>
      <p class="lead mb-4 text-justify">
        Still not clear how to live on a boat? Don't worry, we will send you
        joining instructions and explain everything the day you come aboard.
